post_text:
The Maryland Board of Education met yesterday and voted that, for the 2020-2021 school year, schools are required to provide 180 days of instruction for students, with six hours in a typical school day. Of the six hours, 3.5 must be synchronous (real-time) instruction for grades K-12. For half-day pre-kindergarten, instruction must include a minimum 1.5 hours of synchronous instruction, spread over the course of the half day.

School systems with plans not to return students to schools in person until second semester should reevaluate their reopening plans by the end of the first quarter (after nine weeks) and submit plans to the Maryland State Department of Education by the third week of November.

As always, FCPS will keep our families and community informed of updates that may affect school schedules via FindOutFirst email and online at www.fcps.org.
https://fcps.ezcommunicator.net/edu/frederick/preview_message.aspx?type=notice&app=0&id=92962

post_text:
FCPS is extending free "to go" breakfast and lunch service through December 2020 to all children ages 18 and younger, following recent approval from the United States Department of Agriculture.

FCPS will also provide meals for adults 19 and older who are enrolled in an FCPS program for people with disabilities.

26 schools will provide the free meals, continuing to follow the Summer Food Service Program guidelines, with no need for children to be enrolled in a Frederick County public school.
Parents may pick up a student's meal.

Details: https://fcps.ezcommunicator.net/edu/frederick/preview_message.aspx?app=0&id=92959&type=notice&source=ViewNews

The Board of Education of Frederick County meets this Wednesday, August 19 at 3 PM via teleconference.

The public may view the meeting via FCPS TV at Comcast channel 18 and online at https://www.fcps.org/centraloffice/fcps-television.

Should anyone wish to provide public comment, please send an email that includes your full name to: FCPSBoEmtg@fcps.org the day of the meeting.

Attention FCPS Parents/Guardians!

You should have received an email yesterday with a link to the questionnaire Next School Year Inventory for Parents.
It is important that you complete this questionnaire, as it seeks to collect valuable information specific to your child to assist our planning efforts for the upcoming 2020-2021 school year. This survey will remain open until Monday, June 22.

Your responses will help to enhance and guide the future work of FCPS.

More information: http://ow.ly/f3rv50A9t05

*Please contact your child's school if you have not received the survey via email.

post_text:
It's Time to Register New Students and Apply for Pre-K!

Registration for the FCPS Fall 2020 Kindergarten and applications for Pre-K classes opened June 1, online for the first time. Schools strongly encourage early enrollment so they have time to predict accurate class size and hire adequate staff.

Students already attending an FCPS Pre-K program do not need to register for kindergarten; the school system already has their forms on file.

FCPS also encourages students new to the area and planning to attend any grade 1-12 to register now online.

See more enrollment information here: http://ow.ly/9Abn50zXUmd

CTC Online Application - 2nd Round

FCPS Career & Technology Center is at Frederick County Career & Technology Center.
April 30 at 12:58 PM ¬∑ Frederick, MD ¬∑

FCPS Maryland HIGH SCHOOL Students CURRENTLY in Grades 9, 10, or 11:
FCPS Career & Technology Center is currently accepting applications for our 2ND ROUND - These applications are limited to our OPEN programs for the fall 2020 school year and applications will be accepted on a first come-first served basis.

The programs accepting applications are:
* Advanced Floral Design
* Agribusiness
* Digital Design & Printing Methods
* Landscaping
* Teacher Academy
* Auto Body (applying for waitlist only)
* Automotive Tech (applying for waitlist only)

You may find out detailed information about each program by visiting our website: https://education.fcps.org/ctc/programs

Due to our current COVID-19 situation, we will ONLY accept the online application, which can be found here:
https://pubforms.fcps.org/view.php?id=58196

Starting Monday, April 20, FCPS will distribute meals to go only on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays.

On Mondays, FCPS will distribute meals for Monday and Tuesday.

On Wednesdays, FCPS will distribute meals for Wednesday and Thursday.
On Fridays, FCPS will distribute meals for Friday.

Times are also adjusted to 11 AM-1 PM for all sites.

*In addition, FCPS will discontinue meal service at the St. John's Catholic Prep School, 3989 Buckeystown Pike, Buckeystown, and will open a new drop off location for meals-to-go from a school bus at the Spring Ridge Elementary School parking lot.*

Please see details: http://fcps.anyimage.top/HFeIkcL

post_text:
Schoology Update:
We know you have been experiencing outages and performance issues with Schoology.
We know that these types of issues are inconvenient in a time that is already challenging.

We have been in touch with our Schoology partners this week and feel confident they will make the necessary adjustments to meet this unprecedented demand for distance learning.

Please take a minute to read this statement from Schoology:
https://www.schoology.com/blog/scaling-schoology-increased-demand

FCPS teachers will be flexible with work deadlines during distance learning and even more so in light of the challenges we are seeing with Schoology.
Thank you for exercising patience until Schoology returns to its previous performance levels.

shared_text:
Town of Thurmont
March 18 at 4:07 PM ¬∑

Frederick County Public Schools are distributing free bag lunches for anyone 18 years of age or younger at the Thurmont Elementary School. Look for the school bus in the side parking lot with two FCPS employees handing out the lunch. You do not need to be a student enrolled at FCPS to get a lunch.

The lunch consists of a sandwich, vegetable, fruit and milk. They will be in the TES parking lot from 11:30 am until 12:30 pm Monday through Friday. Currently they are bringing 100 lunches to distribute, if more are needed I am sure they will increase the number. It is important that you make use of this service, a no or low turn out could cause changes in the program.

There was an announcement during our Tuesday town meeting that lunch would be served at Thurmont Middle School, this information was incorrect.

Thanks to FCPS and their staff for making these lunches available for the children in Thurmont and North Frederick County.

As an advisory committee to the Frederick County Board of Education (FCPS), SECAC works closely with school system staff to address the needs of students with disabilities within FCPS. In the same manner, we have been closely monitoring the outbreak of coronavirus (COVID-19) and its potential impact on the SECAC Resource Fair to be held this coming Saturday, March 14 at Rock Creek.



Given the rapidly evolving situation with the COVID-19 virus, we have decided to cancel the SECAC Resource Fair. Our major concern is this event would have included vendor participation which creates a vulnerable environment for our high-risk students with preexisting health and physical needs during the‚Ä¶

Delaplaine Arts Center
March 9 at 2:33 PM ¬∑

The FCPS Maryland All-County Student Art Show is open now through March 29 and features some amazing artworks by local K-12 students! The 2020 Bettie Award Winners and FCPS Faculty Exhibition also are open. Art by FCPS Unified Students is on exhibit in our Community Outreach Gallery, and art by students from St. John Regional Catholic School is on display in our Community Art Gallery. Admission is free!

(Artworks clockwise from top left: "Jacqueline with Flowers" by Chloe Bort, 11th grade, Walkersville High School; "Self-portrait" by Madison Stolz, 1st grade, Walkersville Elementary School; "Charlie" by Seann Bray, 11th grade, Frederick High School; and "Blue Me" by Emma Yoo, 5th grade, Urbana Elementary)
